cs.CG, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the construction of hop spanners for the unit disk graph, which is a problem in computational geometry and wireless ad hoc networks. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of the constructed spanner, which involves results on plane geometry, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with the performance of the constructed spanner, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
